<!--
  passes-isolation library manifest. This module contributes the SHARED isolated-worker
  plumbing (the memfd PfdFactory and the bind/teardown session facade) that :passes-pdf
  and :passes-barcode both consume; it declares NO service of its own. Each consumer
  module declares its own android:isolatedProcess service in its own manifest and names
  the class it binds — this module only supplies the mechanism to bind one.

  ZERO uses-permission entries by design, and it stays that way: the plumbing must add
  nothing to the consumer app's runtime permission set.
-->
